comments: Claxton (BKN) brings his hands toward Wembanyama (SAS) as he moves to set the pick and marginal contact occurs.
Finney-Smith (BKN) firms up on his left foot as he establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Schroder (BKN) quickly slides and releases his arm after placing it on Wembanyama's (SAS) side during the pick.
Thomas (BKN) initiates contact with Wembenyama's (SAS) left wrist that affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
Claxton (BKN) deflects the ball toward the backcourt before Wembenyama (SAS) legally moves to retrieve it.
Claxton (BKN) is retracting his hand from Wembanyama's (SAS) side as he begins his upward shooting motion and any contact is marginal.
Vassell (SAS) moves alongside Schroder's (BKN) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Schroder (BKN) is the last player to touch the ball before it rolls off the backboard and is ruled OOB.
Finney-Smith (BKN) clamps and holds Wembanyama's (SAS) left arm, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
SAS is assessed a delay of game warning during the in-bounds play.
Claxton (BKN) moves alongside Sochan's (SAS) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (BKN) initiates contact with Wembanyama's (SAS) right arm that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Schroder (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball as he raises his arm to contest Sochan's (SAS) shot attempt near the rim.
Finney-Smith (BKN) blocks the ball OOB.
Claxton (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an Wembanyama (SAS).
Claxton (BKN) legally contests Wembanyama's (SAS) layup attempt as the ball is dislodged by the backboard.
Claxton (BKN) establishes himself in Johnson's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Schroder (BKN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes OOB.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a defensive goaltending by Wembenyana (SAS) is overturned and SAS is given possession of the ball.
Schroder (BKN) releases the in-bound pass within 5 seconds.
Claxton (BKN) establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as incidental foot to foot contact occurs.
Johnson's (BKN) right leg naturally drifts slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Jones (SAS) as he contests the jump shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) makes more than marginal contact with Johnson's (SAS) head as Johnson is securing the loose ball.

Johnson (BKN) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Jones' (SAS) head as he secures the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (BKN) commits a take foul on Jones (SAS).
